    • Method Detail

      • load

        public void load()
        Controls how the robot positions itself to receive balls from the dispenser once it has arrived at the specified location. It also directs the loading arm to ensure it is positioned correctly during the loading procedure.

      • launcher3

        public void launcher3(int targetX,
                      int fireLineY)
        Controls how the robot fires the 3 balls it has received from the dispenser. It reloads after each shot, and once all the balls have been fired, the robot resets the loading arm and winch position.
        Parameters:
        targetX - is the grid line position of the target along the x-axis
        fireLineY - is the grid line position of the firing line along the y-axis
